                  <h2 class="font_2" style="font-size:24px;">
                   <span style="font-size:24px;">
                    <span style="font-family:signika,sans-serif;">
                     <a data-content="https://wawexpo2018.auction-bid.org/microsite/" data-type="external" href="https://wawexpo2018.auction-bid.org/microsite/" rel="undefined" target="_blank">
                      <span class="color_14">
                       <span style="font-style:normal;">

                         <span style="font-weight:bold;">

             <div class="txtNew" data-packed="true" id="comp-izbn579c" style="top:1087px;bottom:;left:48px;right:;width:879px;height:auto;position:absolute;margin-left:calc((100% - 980px) * 0.5)">
              <p class="font_7" style="font-size:18px;">
               <span style="font-size:24px;">
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="display:none;">
                 </span>
                 <span style="font-family:nimbus-sans-tw01con, sans-serif;">
                  <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                   Women for Afghan Women (WAW)
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:18px;">
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:nimbus-sans-tw01con, sans-serif;">
                  <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  </span>
                 </span>
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  is a grassroots, human rights organization dedicated to securing and protecting the rights of disenfranchised Afghan women and girls in Afghanistan and New York, particularly their rights to develop their individual potential, to self-determination, and to be represented in all areas of life: political, social, cultural and economic.
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_7" style="font-size:18px;">
               <span style="font-size:18px;">
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  <span class="wixGuard">
                   ​
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_7" style="font-size:18px;">
               <span style="font-size:18px;">
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  WAW was founded in New York in April 2001 in response to the brutal conditions Afghan women and girls were suffering under Taliban rule. After the September 2011 attacks in the United States and the ousting of the Taliban in Afghanistan, the organization has evolved from a small network of volunteers assisting Afghan refugee women in New York into an
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span style="color:rgb(204, 71, 114);">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                   over
                   <span class="color_15">
                    <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                    </span>
                   </span>
                   750-member team
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  that today operates
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span style="color:rgb(204, 71, 114);">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                   programs and 32 facilities across 14 provinces
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  in Afghanistan, a
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 <span style="color:rgb(204, 71, 114);">
                  <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                   community center in New York
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  , and an
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span style="color:rgb(204, 71, 114);">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                   advocacy office in Washington, DC
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  .
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_7" style="font-size:18px;">
               <br/>
               <span style="font-size:18px;">
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  Today, WAW is the largest women’s organization in Afghanistan providing mediation, protection, and life-saving services to women, girls, children, and their families. We are constantly expanding, adapting, and improving the scope of our services to meet ever changing needs and constantly shifting conditions in Afghan society.
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_7" style="font-size:18px;">
               <br/>
               <span style="font-size:18px;">
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  In the United States, WAW’s New York Community Center (NYCC) has become a lifeline and second home to the Afghan immigrant and Afghan-American community. Supported by our advocacy efforts in Washington, DC, we serve the direct needs of this under-served population in the United States by providing culturally sensitive, holistic, and immediate support.
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_7" style="font-size:18px;">
              </p>
              <p class="font_7" style="font-size:18px;">
               <span style="font-size:18px;">
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  With these accomplishments, Women for Afghan Women has served over
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 <span style="color:rgb(204, 71, 114);">
                  <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                   30,000 clients
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  and trained over
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 <span style="color:rgb(204, 71, 114);">
                  <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                   330,000 individuals
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
                <span class="color_15">
                 <span style="font-family:helvetica-w01-roman, helvetica-w02-roman, helvetica-lt-w10-roman, sans-serif;">
                  <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  </span>
                  since 2001.
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
             </div>
